2026-02-26T17:35:00.745667Z  INFO session_loop{thread_id=019c9aee-4d8e-7b70-900e-80cec48c1efd}: codex_core::stream_events_utils: ToolCall: exec_command {"cmd":"cat > .specify/memory/constitution.md <<'EOF'\n<!--\nSync Impact Report\n- Version change: unversioned template -> 1.0.0\n- Modified principles:\n  - [PRINCIPLE_1_NAME] -> I. CLI Contract Is Stable\n  - [PRINCIPLE_2_NAME] -> II. Theme Data Consistency Is Mandatory\n  - [PRINCIPLE_3_NAME] -> III. Tests Protect Behavior (NON-NEGOTIABLE)\n  - [PRINCIPLE_4_NAME] -> IV. Observability and Explicit Failures\n  - [PRINCIPLE_5_NAME] -> V. Simplicity and Reviewable Changes\n- Added sections:\n  - Operational Constraints\n  - Development Workflow & Quality Gates\n- Removed sections:\n  - None\n- Templates requiring updates:\n  - ✅ updated `.specify/templates/plan-template.md`\n  - ✅ updated `.specify/templates/spec-template.md`\n  - ✅ updated `.specify/templates/tasks-template.md`\n  - ⚠ pending `.specify/templates/commands/*.md` (directory not present in this repository)\n  - ✅ updated `README.md`\n- Follow-up TODOs:\n  - TODO(RATIFICATION_DATE): Original ratification date is not recorded in repository history.\n-->\n# SassyAI Constitution\n\n## Core Principles\n\n### I. CLI Contract Is Stable\n- The CLI command set (`:help`, `:themes`, `:mode`, `:random`, `:stats`, `:info`, `:exit`) MUST\n  remain backward compatible unless a deprecation is documented in `README.md` before removal.\n- User-visible prompt and response framing MUST keep theme context and assistant attribution so\n  behavior remains scriptable and understandable.\n- Any change to command semantics MUST include updated CLI tests in `sassy_ai/tests/`.\n\nRationale: The interactive CLI is the product surface and its stability protects user trust.\n\n### II. Theme Data Consistency Is Mandatory\n- Theme identifiers MUST stay synchronized across `sassy_ai/main_cli.py`,\n  `sassy_ai/sassy_core/engine.py`, and `sassy_ai/config/*.json`.\n- New or renamed themes MUST define prompt, color, and emoji metadata plus mapped response\n  intent and pattern coverage.\n- Required configuration files MUST load explicitly; missing required files are errors, not silent\n  fallbacks.\n\nRationale: The assistant relies on coordinated theme metadata and response data to function.\n\n### III. Tests Protect Behavior (NON-NEGOTIABLE)\n- Behavior changes MUST start with a failing or newly added test that captures expected outcome.\n- Pull requests MUST pass `pytest --cov=sassy_ai` with coverage at or above the configured floor\n  (`fail_under = 80`).\n- Regressions in command parsing, theme routing, or response selection MUST include dedicated\n  regression tests.\n\nRationale: Automated tests are the primary defense against regressions in a text-driven product.\n\n### IV. Observability and Explicit Failures\n- Any workflow that updates themes/responses via Amazon Q or equivalent tooling MUST record date,\n  theme, status, and changed artifacts in `sassy_ai/logs/amazon_q_log.md` (or a documented\n  successor log).\n- CLI errors and unknown-command paths MUST return actionable user feedback; silent failures are\n  prohibited.\n- Exceptions from required file reads or invalid config content MUST surface clear failure messages\n  for debugging.\n\nRationale: Fast diagnosis depends on traceable logs and obvious failure modes.\n\n### V. Simplicity and Reviewable Changes\n- Changes MUST prefer straightforward Python and existing dependencies unless a new dependency is\n  justified in the feature plan.\n- Automated content generation MUST result in plain-text, reviewable diffs to code/config files.\n- Solutions MUST favor deterministic behavior over hidden state or implicit side effects.\n\nRationale: Small, explicit changes reduce maintenance cost and improve review quality.\n\n## Operational Constraints\n\n- Runtime target is local CLI execution on Python 3.12 with dependencies listed in\n  `requirements.txt`.\n- Theme and response data are source-controlled JSON assets in `sassy_ai/config/`; ad-hoc runtime\n  formats are not allowed without constitution amendment.\n- The product persona is sarcastic, but contributions MUST avoid hateful or abusive content that\n  targets protected characteristics.\n\n## Development Workflow & Quality Gates\n\n1. Define scope in `spec.md`, including CLI contract impact, theme/data changes, and logging impact.\n2. Add or update failing tests before implementation for each behavior change.\n3. Implement the smallest viable change set and keep config/code mappings synchronized.\n4. Run `pytest --cov=sassy_ai` and relevant linting before requesting review.\n5. Update user and operator docs (`README.md`, logs, quickstart/spec artifacts) when behavior\n   changes.\n6. Reviewers MUST block merges when any Constitution principle is violated without an approved,\n   documented exception.\n\n## Governance\n\n- This Constitution takes precedence over conflicting workflow notes or templates.\n- Amendments require a pull request that includes: proposed change text, impacted templates/docs,\n  migration steps (if any), and version bump rationale.\n- Versioning policy for this document follows semantic intent:\n  - MAJOR: Removes or redefines a principle in a backward-incompatible way.\n  - MINOR: Adds a new principle/section or materially expands governance requirements.\n  - PATCH: Clarifies wording, fixes typos, or improves precision without changing obligations.\n- Compliance review is required in every implementation plan and pull request; unresolved\n  violations block approval.\n\n**Version**: 1.0.0 | **Ratified**: TODO(RATIFICATION_DATE): Original adoption date not recorded | **Last Amended**: 2026-02-26\nEOF"} thread_id=019c9aee-4d8e-7b70-900e-80cec48c1efd
2026-02-26T17:35:06.683092Z  INFO session_loop{thread_id=019c9aee-4d8e-7b70-900e-80cec48c1efd}: codex_core::stream_events_utils: ToolCall: exec_command {"cmd":"python - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\npath = Path('.specify/templates/plan-template.md')\ntext = path.read_text()\nold = \"[Gates determined based on constitution file]\"\nnew = \"- **CLI Contract Gate**: Identify command/prompt/output changes and confirm backward compatibility or documented deprecation.\\n- **Theme Data Gate**: List all synchronized updates across `sassy_ai/main_cli.py`, `sassy_ai/sassy_core/engine.py`, and `sassy_ai/config/*.json`.\\n- **Test Gate**: Define failing-first tests and confirm `pytest --cov=sassy_ai` remains at or above coverage floor.\\n- **Observability Gate**: Capture logging/error-path updates required by the changed behavior.\\n- **Simplicity Gate**: Justify any new dependency or complexity with explicit alternatives considered.\"\nif old not in text:\n    raise SystemExit('target text not found')\npath.write_text(text.replace(old, new))\nPY"} thread_id=019c9aee-4d8e-7b70-900e-80cec48c1efd
